  "prompt": "Since LinkedIn got rid of ask the expert, is Quora now the best place to get expert answers?",
  "response": "While LinkedIn has discontinued its \"Ask the Expert\" feature, there are still several platforms where you can seek expert advice and answers. Quora is one option where you can find answers from a wide range of professionals and enthusiasts on various topics. However, whether it is the \"best\" place depends on your specific needs and preferences.\n\nHere are a few other platforms where you can seek expert advice:\n\n1. **Reddit**: Subreddits like r/AskScience, r/AskHistorians, and r/AskEngineers can be valuable resources for expert insights.\n\n2. **Stack Exchange**: This network of Q&A communities covers diverse fields such as programming (Stack Overflow), mathematics (Math Stack Exchange), and academia (Academia Stack Exchange).\n\n3. **Specialized Forums**: Many industries have niche forums or communities where experts frequently engage. For example, GitHub for developers or ResearchGate for academics.\n\n4. **Twitter**: Following experts in your field and engaging with them can sometimes lead to valuable exchanges.\n\n5. **Medium**: Many professionals and experts publish articles on Medium, offering deep dives into specific topics.\n\n6. **Professional Associations**: Many industries have professional associations that offer forums, webinars, and other resources for expert advice.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" platform depends on the subject matter and the type of engagement you're looking for. Each platform has its strengths, and you might find that a combination of them suits your needs best.",
